<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  {% include 'head' %}
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      {% include 'masthead' %}

      <div class="panel {{panel_class}}">
        <div class="panel-heading"><h2>{{ plan | capitalize }} Plan</h2></div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <h2>7 Easy Steps</h2>
          <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item {{ list_group_item_class }}"><span class="badge">&rarr;</span>Step 1: Transform</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Step 2: Save</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Step 3: Import</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Step 4: Download Images</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Step 5: Rename Images</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Step 6: Upload Images</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Step 7: Money</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <h2>Step 1: Transform</h2>
          {% if message %}
          <h2 class="danger">{{ message }}</h2>
          {% endif %}
          {% include 'upload' %}
        </div>

        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <h2>Terms and Conditions</h2>
          <div class="checkbox">
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" checked="checked" class="disabled"> Based on my honor as a gentleman/lady, I swear to pay <span type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-success">${{price}}</span> should I find Mount Exodus useful and satisifying.
            </label>
          </div>
          <div class="checkbox">
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" checked="checked" class="disabled"> Payment will be made via Paypal upon completion of testing and deployment of content converted from TypePad to WordPress.  The image download and renaming tasks are left as an exercise to the client.
            </label>
          </div>
          <div class="checkbox">
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" checked="checked" class="disabled"> Failure to pay will earn a spot on the Mount Exodus Wall of Shame.  Each Wall of Shame recipient will earn a link to several of your random posts with deeply disturbing comments about your mother and various beasts of burden.  You've been warned.  Don't be a dick.  <a href="http://vimeo.com/22053820" target="_new">F*ck&nbsp;you!&nbsp;Pay&nbsp;Me.</a>
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-12">
          <div class="panel {{panel_class}}">
            <div class="panel-heading">
              <h3 class="panel-title">Pay Up!</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="panel-body">
              <div style="float:right;">
                <h3>&nbsp;</h3>
                {% if plan == 'personal' %}
                  {% include 'paypal29' %}
                {% elsif plan == 'professional' %}
                  {% include 'paypal49' %}
                {% else %}
                  {% include 'paypal69' %}
                {% endif %}
              </div>
              <h3>Pay <span type="button" class="btn btn-success">${{price}}</span> if you are satisified with the Mount Exodus Moveable Type to WordPress conversion utility.</h3>
              <p><b>You're an assh*le!</b>  Why the f*ck did you append a Google Analytics tag in my posts?<br /> I needed some way to generate metrics and discover dishonorable bastards too cheap to pay for services rendered.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% include 'footer' %}
    </div> <!-- /container -->
  </body>
</html>